he%20US%20median%20home-sale%20price%20could%20be%20%241%20million%2C%20according%20to%20a%20forecast%20from%20NAR's%20economist.%3Cp%3Ed3sign%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EData%20from%20NAR%20shows%20the%20median%20sale%20price%20of%20an%20existing%20home%20was%20%24429%2C300%20in%20June.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20median%20single-family%20home%20sale%20price%20could%20hit%20%241%20million%20by%202050%2C%20according%20to%20an%20economist.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20climb%20to%20%241%20million%20will%20be%20slow%2C%20so%20buyers%20should%20expect%20modest%20price%20gains%20for%20now%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI%20know%20it%2C%20and%20you%20know%20it%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fhow-to-buy-a-house-step-by-step-guide%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebuying%20a%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20never%20felt%20this%20unaffordable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20prospective%20buyers%20have%20faced%20a%20punishing%20mix%20of%20too%20few%20homes%20for%20sale%2C%20high%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Faverage-mortgage-interest-rate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emortgage%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20persistently%20high%20home%20prices.%20Those%20pressures%20have%20pushed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhomeowners-struggle-hidden-real-estate-costs-insurance-property-taxes-fees-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehomeownership%20out%20of%20reach%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20many%20Americans.%20Unfortunately%2C%20affordability%20could%20get%20even%20worse%20in%20the%20years%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20an%20economic%20forum%20during%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Real%20Estate%20Editors%20conference%20in%20June%2C%20National%20Association%20of%20Realtors%20chief%20economist%20Lawrence%20Yun%20told%20a%20room%20full%20of%20journalists%20that%20he%20expects%20the%20median%20single-family%20home%20sale%20price%20to%20reach%20%241%20million%20by%202050.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20comparison%2C%20the%20median%20sale%20price%20of%20an%20existing%20home%20was%20%24429%2C300%20in%20June%2C%20according%20to%20NAR%20data.%20Yun%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20while%20his%202050%20forecast%20is%20speculative%2C%20it%20is%20based%20on%20steady%20annual%20home-price%20growth%20of%203%25%20to%204%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20worth%20looking%20back%3A%20for%20example%2C%20back%20in%201990%2C%20the%20median%20national%20home%20price%20was%20barely%20above%20%24100%2C000%2C%26quot%3B%20Yun%20said.%20%26quot%3BAt%20that%20time%2C%20people%20would%20not%20have%20envisioned%20that%20today's%20home%20prices%20could%20be%20%24400%2C000.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20pointed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsan-francisco-housing-market-real-estate-home-prices-ai-boom-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eto%20San%20Francisco's%20housing%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20another%20example.%20%26quot%3BIn%20San%20Francisco%2C%20a%20million-dollar%20home%20is%20very%20common%20today%2C%20but%20back%20in%201990%2C%20the%20median%20home%20price%20in%20San%20Francisco%20was%20about%20%24250%2C000%2C%20and%20I'm%20sure%20no%20one%20was%20thinking%20about%20a%20million%2C%26quot%3B%20Yun%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYun's%20forecast%20is%20sobering%2C%20especially%20as%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20real%20estate%20market%20appear%20to%20be%20normalizing.%20Home-price%20growth%20has%20slowed%20in%20formerly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-from-austin-texas-to-new-york-city-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehot%20markets%C2%A0like%20Austin%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20San%20Diego%2C%20while%20new%20home%20construction%20in%20smaller%20markets%20like%20Kaufman%2C%20Texas%2C%20and%20Harnett%2C%20North%20Carolina%2C%20has%20helped%20boost%20sales.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYun%20said%20those%20cities%20are%20outliers%20in%20a%20national%20real%20estate%20market%20still%20defined%20by%20climbing%20prices%20and%20soft%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPlaces%20like%20Austin%2C%20or%20any%20local%20market%2C%20will%20deviate%20from%20national%20trends%20for%20some%20time.%20But%20Austin's%20price%20decline%20is%20pretty%20much%20due%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20had%20a%20spectacular%20run-up%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BOne%20wonders%2C%20after%20a%20little%20pause%20in%20Austin%2C%20whether%20it%20will%20begin%20to%20show%20that%20superstar%20status%20again.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYun%20said%20it%20will%20take%20years%20of%20steady%20gains%20for%20the%20US%20median%20single-family%20home%20sale%20price%20to%20reach%20%241%20million.%20For%20now%2C%20he%20expects%20prices%20to%20rise%20only%20moderately.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20short%20term%2C%20I%20think%20home%20prices%20will%20see%20a%20very%20minimal%20gain%20this%20year%20%E2%80%94%20maybe%201%25%2C%202%25%2C%20or%203%25%20nationwide%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20would%20be%20below%20consumer%20price%20inflation%20and%20below%20income%20growth%2C%20since%20incomes%20are%20rising%20around%203%25%20to%204%25.%20I%20think%20home-price%20growth%20coming%20in%20slightly%20below%20income%20growth%20is%20a%20healthy%20thing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmedian-usa-home-could-cost-1-million-by-2050-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1781035956000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a282c27208d75cc7b791cdb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmedian-usa-home-could-cost-1-million-by-2050-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20home%20prices%20continue%20rising%20at%20an%20annual%20pace%20of%203%25%20to%204%25%2C%20%241%20million%20could%20become%20the%20new%20threshold%20for%20homeownershi