hor%22%3A%22Ethan%20Shanfeld%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22She%20received%20a%20%2412%2C000%20basic%20income.%20Three%20years%20later%2C%20she's%20a%20mom%20of%20six%20and%20moving%20to%20a%20bigger%20apartment.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Taniquewa%20Brewster%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a285f98208d75cc7b79280f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221152%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETaniquewa%20Brewster%2C%2041%2C%20is%20a%20former%20basic%20income%20participant%20in%20Austin%2C%20Texas.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Taniquewa%20Brewster%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETaniquewa%20Brewster%20received%20%241%2C000%20a%20month%20for%20one%20year%20from%20an%20Austin%20basic%20income%20program.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20landed%20job%20certifications%20and%20stable%20housing%2C%20but%20is%20worried%20about%20emergency%20expenses.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUS%20cities%20have%20run%20hundreds%20of%20pilots%20offering%20no-strings-attached%20cash%20to%20low-income%20families.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETaniquewa%20Brewster%20is%20an%20assistant%20property%20manager%2C%20doula%2C%20student%2C%20advocate%2C%20and%20proud%20mom%20of%20six.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2041-year-old%20is%20also%20a%20former%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flife-after-basic-income-more-savings-working-two-jobs-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eguaranteed%20basic%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%20participant%20in%20her%20hometown%20of%20Austin%2C%20Texas.%20She%20was%20one%20of%20135%20low-income%20households%20that%20received%20%241%2C000%20a%20month%20for%20a%20year%2C%20from%20September%202022%20to%20August%202023.%20The%20money%20helped%20her%20cover%20bills%2C%20build%20savings%2C%20and%20land%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbasic-income-helps-people-get-jobs-earn-higher-pay-gbi-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emore%20stable%20career%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20first%20spoke%20with%20Brewster%20in%20the%20fall%20of%202024%2C%20about%20a%20year%20after%20her%20cash%20payments%20ended.%20She's%20now%20feeling%20more%20confident%20in%20her%20family's%20future%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20unexpected%20bills%20remain%20a%20stressor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20been%20able%20to%20keep%20my%20children%20from%20having%20to%20work%20to%20contribute%20to%20the%20household%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20in%20June.%20%26quot%3BThey%20can%20do%20whatever%20they%20want%20to%20do%20with%20their%20money%2C%20and%20that's%20a%20big%20difference%20for%20me%20%E2%80%94%20breaking%20that%20generational%20curse%20of%20poverty.%26quot%3B%20She%20said%20that%20fear%20is%20no%20longer%20her%20dominant%20emotion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBasic%20income%20gained%20momentum%20in%20the%20early%202020s%20as%20a%20solution%20for%20poverty%20and%20an%20increasingly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-unemployed-dream-jobs-hiring-college-degree-graduation-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI-dominated%20job%20market%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20no-strings-attached%20cash%20model%20has%20been%20tried%20hundreds%20of%20times%20over%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20championed%20by%20lawmakers%2C%20local%20advocates%2C%20and%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-ubi-universal-basic-income-view-changes-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebig-name%20tech%20leaders%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20heard%20from%20single%20parents%20who%20used%20the%20money%20for%20groceries%20and%20families%20who%20secured%20apartments%20after%20years%20of%20instability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20the%20reporting%20and%20data%20about%20basic%20income%20follows%20participants%20during%20and%20immediately%20after%20their%20programs.%20What's%20less%20documented%20is%20how%20families%20fare%20in%20the%20years%20after%20their%20cash%20payments%20end.%20Brewer%20said%20she's%20still%20seeing%20a%20benefit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3A%2520allisonkelly%40buinessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eallisonkelly%40buinessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2281fddc67-621c-4674-aab7-ce93973d1f3e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBrewster%20feels%20more%20financially%20confident%2C%20but%20worries%20about%20emergency%20expenses%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAustin's%20guaranteed%20basic%20income%20program%20was%20a%20collaboration%20between%20the%20city%20and%20the%20nonprofit%20UpTogether.%20Brewster%20qualified%20because%20she%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbasic-income-gbi-ubi-low-income-americans-afford-housing-food-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eexperiencing%20housing%20insecurity%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20earned%20less%20than%2060%25%20of%20the%20area%20median%20family%20income%2C%20which%20was%20slightly%20over%20%2464%2C000%20annually%20for%20her%20household%20size.%20Brewster%20is%20a%20single%20mother%20who%20supports%20her%20children%20%E2%80%94%20now%20between%20infancy%20and%20college%20age%20%E2%80%94%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrior%20to%20GBI%2C%20she%20was%20patching%20together%20low-paying%20part-time%20jobs%20and%20struggling%20to%20pay%20bills.%20She%20said%20the%20financial%20strain%20prevented%20her%20from%20getting%20the%20training%20she%20needed%20for%20a%20higher-paying%20real%20estate%20job%20with%20predictable%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20working%20as%20hard%20as%20I%20could%2C%20working%20overtime%2C%26quot%3B%20Brewster%20said%20in%202024.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20keeping%20me%20away%20from%20my%20family.%20That's%20keeping%20me%20away%20from%20things%20that%20I%20can%20be%20doing%20%E2%80%94%20even%20going%20back%20to%20school%20%E2%80%94%20because%20I%20have%20to%20work%20so%20hard%20to%20just%20cover%20rent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20extra%20%241%2C000%20a%20month%2C%20Brewster%20said%20she%20was%20able%20to%20get%20the%20certifications%20she%20needed%20to%20be%20promoted%20as%20a%20leasing%20agent%20and%20now%20assistant%20property%20manager.%20She%20also%20completed%20her%20doula%20training%20and%20has%20since%20gone%20back%20to%20school%20to%20study%20nonprofit%20management.%20She%20remains%20a%20vocal%20advocate%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsan-antonio-ubi-guaranteed-basic-income-housing-finances-austin-rent-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebasic%20income%20in%20Texas%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Building%20a%20career%20that%20both%20supports%20her%20family%20and%20allows%20her%20to%20support%20others%20is%20a%20dream%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe's%20currently%20adopting%20her%20youngest%20daughter%2C%20whom%20she's%20been%20fostering%2C%20and%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3Eher%20family%20is%20preparing%20to%20move%20to%20a%20bigger%20apartment.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finfo.uptogether.org%2Faustincasestudy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EData%20from%20the%20Austin%20pilot%20%3C%2Fa%3Eshows%20that%20the%20majority%20of%20participants%20were%20better%20able%20to%20afford%20basic%20necessities%20and%20pay%20off%20debt%20during%20and%20directly%20after%20the%20pilot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20didn't%20just%20help%20me%20financially%2C%20it%20gave%20me%20confidence%20in%20myself%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20hand%20up%20and%20not%20a%20handout.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20the%20payments%20didn't%20fix%20all%20of%20her%20affordability%20concerns.%20She%20had%20an%20unexpected%20illness%20last%20year%20that%20required%20expensive%20medications%20and%20hospital%20care.%20She%20has%20some%20savings%2C%20but%20worries%20about%20what%20will%20happen%20if%20her%20family%20runs%20into%20more%20emergency%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20other%20GBI%20pilots%2C%20Brewster's%20program%20was%20designed%20to%20provide%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funiversal-basic-income-pros-and-cons%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eshort-term%20financial%20support%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Austin's%20program%20stopped%20recently%20due%20to%20a%20funding%20lapse%20and%20limited%20political%20backing.%20The%20US%20has%20yet%20to%20try%20basic%20income%20for%20more%20than%20a%20few%20years%20at%20a%20time%2C%20largely%20because%20governments%20and%20philanthropists%20say%20they%20can't%20fund%20it%20long-term.%20Some%20tech%20leaders%20who%20previously%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-ubi-universal-basic-income-view-changes-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echampioned%20basic%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20displaced%20workers%20now%20say%C2%A0the%20impact%20doesn't%20justify%20the%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECritics%20of%20basic%20income%20also%20say%20cash%20payments%20discourage%20participants%20from%20working%20to%20earn%20a%20paycheck%2C%20and%20that%20the%20programs%20require%20too%20much%20capital%20to%20operate%20alongside%20other%20safety%20net%20programs%2C%20like%20SNAP%20and%20Medicaid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20for%20Brewster%2C%20even%20a%20year%20of%20no-strings-attached%20cash%20was%20life-changing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20felt%20like%20people%20were%20actually%20asking%20me%20what%20my%20needs%20were%2C%20and%20how%20they%20could%20help%20me%20meet%20those%20needs%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20something%20comforting%20about%20someone%20actually%20caring%20enough%20to%20ask.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flife-after-basic-income-better-job-apartment-worried-about-bills-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A178103317500