Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20heard%20just%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsurprising-pregnancy-symptoms-2018-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eevery%20comment%3C%2Fa%3E%20you%20can%20think%20of%2C%20and%20it's%20been%20going%20on%20ever%20since%20I%20was%20pregnant.%20I%20would%20be%20at%20the%20dentist%2C%20for%20example%2C%20and%20have%20to%20put%20on%20the%20consultation%20form%20that%20I%20was%20pregnant%2C%20only%20for%20the%20receptionist%20to%20do%20a%20double%20take.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20that%20really%20hurt%20was%20being%20out%20at%20a%20restaurant%20for%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcheap-one-pot-dinner-recipes-from-professional-meal-planner-mom%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efamily%20dinner%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20Christmas%2C%20when%20the%20server%20complimented%20us%20for%20spending%20quality%20time%20with%20our%20%26quot%3Bgrandson.%26quot%3B%20The%20assumption%20that%20we%20are%20our%20son's%20grandparents%20happens%20pretty%20much%20every%20time%20we%20go%20out%2C%20whether%20it's%20to%20the%20park%2C%20a%20toddler%20group%2C%20or%20even%20while%20shopping.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c627c83d-a4a4-4d71-8529-83250b4ee02e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20end%20up%20sharing%20our%20painful%20backstory%20with%20strangers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20I%20can%20keep%20my%20cool%2C%20but%20other%20times%20it%20really%20hurts%20that%20people%20just%20make%20assumptions%2C%20because%20we%20waited%20so%20long%20to%20have%20our%20son.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20becomes%20expected%20that%20we%20share%20our%20very%20painful%2C%20personal%20back%20story%3A%20that%20we%20have%20been%20trying%20to%20conceive%20since%20I%20was%2039%2C%20and%20I%20have%20experienced%20seven%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freference%2Fsigns-of-an-early-miscarriage%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edevastating%20miscarriages%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Our%20son%20is%20the%20miracle%20we%20were%20waiting%20for%20over%2014%20years.%20Having%20to%20share%20this%20with%20strangers%20isn't%20easy%2C%20but%20it%20feels%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20our%20son%20currently%20sees%20is%20two%20parents%20who%20love%20him%20immensely.%20He%20doesn't%20see%20our%20ages%2C%20but%20I'm%20worried%20this%20will%20come%20when%20he%20starts%20school.%20I%20don't%20want%20his%20friends%20to%20judge%20him%20and%20tease%20him%20for%20having%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbeing-an-older-parent-pros-cons-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eolder%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20I%20am%20actually%20thinking%20of%20homeschooling%20him%2C%20to%20protect%20him%20from%20bullying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22eaa91b73-701c-4fe7-a722-c4c7fa446fe8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAs%20older%20parents%2C%20we%20don't%20take%20our%20health%20for%20granted%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20a%20young%20child%20at%20this%20age%20means%20you%20don't%20take%20anything%20for%20granted.%20I%20have%20been%20a%20nutritionist%20for%20over%2020%20years%2C%20seeing%20clients%20across%20London%2C%20where%20we%20live%3B%20Vienna%2C%20where%20I'm%20originally%20from%3B%20and%20Los%20Angeles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20we%20ended%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-ivf-2018-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econceiving%20through%20IVF%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I'm%20convinced%20that%20nutrition%20played%20a%20strong%20part%20in%20helping%20me%20fall%20pregnant%20at%20the%20age%20of%2053%2C%20and%20getting%20through%20menopause%20when%20I%20started%20experiencing%20hot%20flashes%20when%20I%20was%2055%2C%20delayed%20because%20of%20the%20IVF%20hormones.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20now%2C%20nutrition%20is%20what%20keeps%20me%20fit%20enough%20to%20match%20my%20son's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-save-your-energy-for-things-that-matter-2011-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eenergy%20levels%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20also%20not%20just%20about%20the%20present.%20Naturally%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20want%20to%20live%20as%20long%20as%20possible%20to%20be%20here%20for%20our%20son%2C%20so%20that's%20another%20reason%20we%20want%20to%20take%20care%20of%20our%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20family%2C%20we%20eat%20a%20fully%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freference%2Fis-organic-food-better-for-you%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eorganic%20diet%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20I%20cook%20fresh%20meals%20at%20home%20as%20often%20as%20possible.%20I%20make%20sure%20every%20meal%20contains%20protein%2C%20vegetables%2C%20and%20either%20rye%20bread%20or%20rice%20noodles.%20A%20typical%20meal%20for%20my%20son%20would%20be%20a%20boiled%20egg%20with%20kefir%2C%20a%20fermented%20milk%20drink%2C%20some%20boiled%2C%20sliced%20vegetables%2C%20avocado%2C%20and%20a%20side%20of%20banana%20chips%20and%20rye%20bread.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20week%2C%20I%20make%20a%20large%20portion%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freference%2Fbone-broth-benefits%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebone%20broth%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20cooking%20it%20for%20up%20to%2012%20hours%20before%20cooling%20it%20and%20decanting%20it%20into%20toddler%20bottles%2C%20which%20I%20then%20serve%20daily%20to%20my%20son.%20I'm%20confident%20it's%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20he's%20hardly%20been%20sick.%20My%20husband%20Peter%20and%20I%20both%20regularly%20have%20bone%20broth%20too%2C%20and%20my%20elderly%20dad%20in%20Austria%20has%20also%20started%20having%20it.%20I've%20even%20gotten%20my%20nephew%20and%20his%20children%20onto%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20take%20several%20supplements.%20I've%20also%20taken%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftried-seven-types-pilates-strength-toning-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereformer%20pilates%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20build%20strength.%20And%20we%20try%20to%20get%20as%20much%20sleep%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a8db5317-3adb-45ca-ae6f-78271ea69631%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20really%20enjoy%20my%20time%20with%20my%20son%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20had%20a%20long%20time%20to%20think%20about%20how%20I%20want%20to%20balance%20work%20with%20spending%20time%20with%20my%20son%2C%20as%20it's%20important%20to%20me%20to%20spend%20as%20much%20time%20with%20him%20as%20possible%20while%20keeping%20my%20nutrition%20business%20going.%20I%20took%20a%20step%20back%20from%20my%20business%20when%20my%20son%20was%20born%2C%20seeing%20clients%20only%20when%20they%20approached%20me%20%E2%80%94%20I%20didn't%20do%20any%20proactive%20marketing%20again%20until%20this%20year.%20My%20husband%20runs%20his%20own%20small%20advertising%20agency%2C%20so%20he%20had%20some%20flexibility%20to%20step%20in%20and%20take%20care%20of%20our%20son%20when%20needed%2C%20and%20we%20also%20use%20a%20babysitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20our%20babysitter%20comes%20for%20about%20half%20the%20day%2C%20and%20I%20take%20care%20of%20Lewis%20myself%20for%20the%20other%20half.%20That's%20the%20other%20thing%20you%20have%20to%20think%20about%20when%20you%20start%20a%20family%20at%20this%20age%20-%20you%20can't%20rely%20on%20grandparents%20to%20help.%20They%20have%20either%20died%20already%20or%20are%20too%20old%20to%20have%20the%20physical%20strength%20and%20mental%20capacity%20to%20take%20care%20of%20a%20toddler.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20really%20enjoy%20my%20time%20with%20my%20son%2C%20though%2C%20and%20I%20hope%20he%20does%20too.%20I%20take%20him%20to%20toddler%20activities%20like%20golf%2C%20gymnastics%2C%20and%20soccer.%20When%20he%20takes%20a%20nap%2C%20I%20try%20to%20lie%20down%20with%20him%20to%20rest%20and%20be%20near%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20frustrating%20that%20so%20many%20people%20think%20it's%20OK%20to%20make%20the%20insensitive%20comments%20that%20they%20do.%20You%20don't%20know%20what%20someone%20else%20has%20been%20through.%20It's%20nobody's%20business%20how%20old%20we%20are.%20We%20are%20doing%20the%20best%20for%20our%20son%2C%20and%20that%20is%20what%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhad-son-at-53-mistaken-for-grandma-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1781031182000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a173b78b4fb977f35980569%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhad-son-at-53-mistaken-for-grandma-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Monica%20Kranner%20says%20becoming%20a%20mother%20in%20her%2050s%20after%20years%20of%20infertility%20has%20brought%20both%20joy%20and%20painful%20public%20judgment.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(MaryLou%20Costa)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%202%20sisters%20turned%20a%20love%20of%20vintage%20lockers%20into%20an%20eight-figure%20business%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mustard%20Made's%20co-founders%20Becca%20and%20Jess%20Stern%20posing%20in%20front%20of%20their%20brand's%20colorful%20lockers.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a22f26db4fb977f35984cf7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJess%20and%20nd%20Becca%20Stern%20are%20the%20founders%20of%20Mustard%20Made.%3Cp%3EAyesha%20Kazim%20and%20Isabella%20Moore%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBecca%20and%20Jess%20Stern%20launched%20a%20locker%20brand%20in%202018%20with%20%2425%2C000%20and%20no%20industry%20knowledge.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20sisters%20built%20an%20eight-figure%20global%20brand%20by%20refusing%20to%20chase%20trends.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETheir%20%26quot%3Bthink%20x%2010%26quot%3B%20rule%20pushed%20them%20to%20make%20big%20operational%20bets%20early%20on.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EBecca%20Stern%20loved%20buying%20vintage%20lockers%2C%20but%20found%20they%20weren't%20very%20practical%20for%20home%20storage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20and%20her%20sister%2C%20Jess%20Stern%2C%20had%20often%20talked%20about%20starting%20a%20business%20together%20and%20saw%20an%20opportunity%20to%20reinvent%20them%20into%20something%20beautiful%20and%20functional%20for%20people%20to%20use%20in%20their%20homes.%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224326%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20set%20of%20Mustard%20Made%20lockers.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a22e42e2e5a80cfe0503d55%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225407%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20sisters%20put%20about%20%2425%2C000%20AUD%20of%20their%20own%20savings%20into%20branding%2C%20samples%2C%20and%20a%20stand%20at%20a%20trade%20show%20in%20Sydney%3Cp%3EAyesha%20Kazim%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnce%20we%20made%20the%20decision%20to%20start%2C%20things%20moved%20quickly%2C%26quot%3B%20Becca%20said.%20The%20sisters%20were%20working%20with%20no%20product%20development%20knowledge%20and%20no%20outside%20funding.%20They%20also%20overlapped%20for%20only%20a%20few%20hours%20each%20day%2C%20as%20Becca%20worked%20from%20Australia%20while%20raising%20her%20new%20baby%2C%20and%20Jess%20worked%20from%20the%20UK%20on%20the%20side%20of%20her%20full-time%20job.%20%26quot%3BThere%20were%20lots%20of%20late-night%20calls%20and%20the%20feeling%20that%20we%20were%20always%20swimming%20in%20the%20deep%20end%2C%20constantly%20hitting%20new%20challenges%20and%20figuring%20out%20the%20best%20way%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Becca%20Stern%2C%20co-founder%20of%20Mustard%20Made%2C%20holds%20up%20some%20swatches%20in%20their%20Newcastle%20office.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a22e5262e5a80cfe0503d6a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMustard%20Made%20has%20nearly%2040%20employees.%3Cp%3EIsabella%20Moore%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20within%20a%20few%20months%2C%20they%20were%20in%20China%20meeting%20with%20potential%20manufacturers.%20They%20put%20about%20%2425%2C000%20AUD%20of%20their%20own%20savings%20into%20branding%2C%20samples%2C%20and%20a%20stand%20at%20a%20trade%20show%20in%20Sydney%2C%20officially%20launching%20their%20brand%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fmustard-made-review%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMustard%20Made%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20the%20world%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20walked%20away%20from%20that%20show%20with%20over%20%24200%2C000%20AUD%20in%20orders.%20%26quot%3BThat%20was%20the%20moment%20we%20realized%20we%20were%20onto%20something%2C%26quot%3B%20Becca%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20Six%20months%20later%2C%20Jess%20left%20her%20corporate%20career%20to%20go%20all%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20they've%20grown%20into%20a%20thriving%20global%20brand%2C%20spanning%20three%20continents%20with%20a%20team%20of%20nearly%2040%20employees%20and%20bringing%20in%20eight%20figures%20of%20revenue%20a%20year.%20The%20sisters%20told%20Business%20Insider%20about%20the%20two%20pivotal%20decisions%20that%20helped%20them%20expand%20their%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e1a9ba2a-7ee1-44a1-9686-30092e35a499%5C%22%3EThey%20avoided%20trends%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20very%20early%20conversations%20about%20the%20business%2C%20the%20Stern%20sisters%20decided%20they%20wanted%20to%20focus%20on%20timelessness%20over%20trends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20mood%20board%20in%20Mustard%20Made's%20Newcastle%20office.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a22e55c2e5a80cfe0503d70%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20business%20has%20seen%20a%20nearly%2030%25%20return%20customer%20rate%20that%20has%20only%20grown%20over%20time.%3Cp%3EIsabella%20Moore%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20%26quot%3Bobsessive%26quot%3B%20amount%20of%20thought%20and%20energy%20they%20put%20into%20their%20products%2C%20they%20said%20they%20couldn't%20imagine%20selling%20them%20for%20only%20six%20months%20before%20moving%20them%20to%20a%20sale%20section%20and%20phasing%20them%20out.%20They%20also%20questioned%20whether%20trend%20chasing%20really%20worked.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20seen%20in%20the%20industry%20how%20hopping%20on%20trends%20can%20provide%20quick%20and%20exciting%20wins%2C%20but%20they%20can%20also%20date%20your%20product%20very%20quickly%2C%26quot%3B%20Becca%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20clarity%2C%20they%20added%2C%20has%20helped%20them%20build%20a%20brand%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Bcult%20following%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20a%20nearly%2030%25%20return%20customer%20rate%20that%20has%20only%20grown%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224385%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jess%20Stern%2C%20co-founder%20of%20Mustard%20Made%2C%20sitting%20on%20a%20desk%20in%20their%20London%20office.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a22e47eb4fb977f35984c61%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226139%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BBringing%20in%20great%20people%20early%20has%20been%20key%20to%20scaling%20the%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20Jess%20said.%3Cp%3EAyesha%20Kazim%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20see%20something%20go%20viral%2C%20it's%20certainly%20tempting%20to%20think%2C%20'Should%20we%20be%20doing%20that%20too%3F'%26quot%3B%20Jess%20said%2C%20such%20as%20when%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcharli-xcx-brat-autumn-remix-album-explained-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBrat%20Green%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbarbie-set-used-so-much-pink-paint-caused-international-shortage-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBarbie%20Pink%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20were%20taking%20over%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20sisters%20said%20they%20want%20to%20stay%20close%20to%20the%20intentional%20design%20customers%20have%20come%20to%20love%20and%20expect%20from%20the%20business.%20They%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20they%20still%20sell%20every%20product%20and%20color%20they%20have%20ever%20launched%2C%20except%20for%20a%20limited%20rainbow%20launch%20in%202024%20to%20raise%20money%20for%20an%20LGBTIQ%2B%20organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226524%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20close%20up%20shot%20of%20some%20Mustard%20Made%20lockers.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a22e4a8b4fb977f35984c68%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224349%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMustard%20Made%20sells%20almost%20every%20product%20and%20color%20ever%20launched.%3Cp%3EAyesha%20Kazim%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGrowth%20can%20sometimes%20dilute%20a%20brand%2C%20but%20we've%20worked%20hard%20to%20ensure%20that%20every%20decision%20still%20feels%20aligned%20with%20who%20we%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20Becca%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d5185d60-7ed6-40be-ba59-25ac82ed6707%5C%22%3EThey%20built%20as%20if%20they%20were%20bigger%20from%20day%20one%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20operations%20side%2C%20the%20sisters%20applied%20an%20internal%20pressure%20test%20they%20call%20%26quot%3Bthink%20x%2010.%26quot%3B%20This%20is%20when%20they%20ask%20whether%20any%20given%20process%2C%20system%2C%20or%20approach%20would%20still%20work%20if%20Mustard%20were%2010%20times%20its%20current%20size.%20%26quot%3BIt%20has%20saved%20us%20so%20many%20headaches%20and%20allowed%20Mustard%20to%20grow%20and%20expand%20globally%2C%26quot%3B%20Becca%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20on%2C%20that%20question%20pushed%20Becca%20and%20Jess%20toward%20a%20decision%20that%20felt%20uncomfortably%20big%20at%20the%20time%3A%20signing%20with%20a%20third-party%20logistics%20provider%20instead%20of%20managing%20warehousing%20from%20a%20shipping%20container%20in%20Becca's%20backyard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Becca%20Stern%2C%20co-founder%20of%20Mustard%20Made%2C%20sits%20at%20her%20office%20desk.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a22e5a22ab5f9757add986d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBecca%20said%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bthinkx10%26quot%3B%20mantra%20gave%20the%20sisters%20the%20confidence%20to%20take%20bigger%20risks.%3Cp%3EIsabella%20Moore%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20feels%20ridiculous%20now%2C%20but%20at%20that%20point%2C%20engaging%20with%20a%20third-party%20logistics%20provider%20felt%20like%20a%20really%20huge%20step%2C%26quot%3B%20Becca%20said.%20The%20%26quot%3Bthink%20x10%26quot%3B%20philosophy%20gave%20them%20the%20confidence%20to%20take%20the%20leap.%20The%20risk%20expanded%20Mustard%20Made's%20ability%20to%20meet%20demand%20and%20scale.%20Now%2C%20the%20business%20has%20four%20third-party%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinmile-ai-last-mile-delivery-optimization-net-zero-trucking-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elogistics%20warehouses%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20plans%20to%20expand%20to%20the%20East%20Coast.%20%26quot%3BIt%20always%20blows%20my%20mind%20to%20see%20that%20the%20scale%20that%20once%20felt%20unachievable%20has%20now%20become%20our%20norm.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20logic%20applies%20to%20hiring.%20%26quot%3BBringing%20in%20great%20people%20early%20has%20been%20key%20to%20scaling%20the%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20Jess%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20hiring%20before%20they%20felt%20ready%2C%20particularly%20in%20areas%20where%20the%20founders%20didn't%20have%20expertise%2C%20is%20what%20allowed%20them%20to%20focus%20on%20the%20strategic%20areas%20of%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Becca%20Stern%2C%20co-founder%20of%20Mustard%20Made%2C%20peers%20out%20from%20one%20of%20her%20lockers.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a22e5d32ab5f9757add9873%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMustard%20Made%20brings%20in%20eight%20figures%20of%20revenue%20per%20year.%3Cp%3EIsabella%20Moore%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBecca%20frames%20the%20business's%20underlying%20mindset%20as%20a%20three-step%20cycle.%20%26quot%3BBe%20optimistic%2C%20then%20pessimistic%2C%20then%20optimistic%20again.%20You%20have%20to%20have%20belief%20and%20hope%20to%20get%20moving%2C%20then%20you%20have%20to%20break%20it%20down%20from%20every%20angle%20to%20find%20all%20the%20possible%20ways%20it%20could%20go%20wrong%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnce%20you've%20planned%20for%20the%20worst-case%20scenarios%2C%20you%20lean%20all%20in%20and%20enjoy%20the%20ride.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmustard-made-founders-business-growth-strategy-2026-06%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1781031066000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a22f26db4fb977f35984cf7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmustard-made-founders-business-growth-strategy-2026-06%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Mustard%20Made%20has%20grown%20into%20a%20thriving%20global%20brand%2C%20spanning%20three%20continents%20with%20a%20team%20of%20nearly%2040%20employees.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Erin%20Greenawald)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Door