alUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fmust-respond-trump-says-us-apache-helicopter-was-shot-down-by-iran-11614072%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fmust-respond-trump-says-us-apache-helicopter-was-shot-down-by-iran-11614072%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fmust-respond-trump-says-us-apache-helicopter-was-shot-down-by-iran-11614072%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20a%20lawyer%20who%20couldn't%20pay%20%24100k%20for%20H-1B%20workers.%20Opportunities%20could%20open%20up%20again%20now%20the%20fee%20has%20been%20scrapped.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224757%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Hung-Lin%20Lai%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a2831b2208d75cc7b791d12%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223567%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHung-Lin%20Lai.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Hung-Lin%20Lai%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EHung-Lin%20Lai%2C%20an%20Oklahoma-based%20lawyer%2C%20welcomed%20a%20judge%20blocking%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffederal-judge-blocks-trump-100-000-h-1b-visa-fee-2026-6%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%20%24100%2C000%20H-1B%20visa%20fee%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELai%20said%20small%20businesses%20like%20his%20will%20likely%20seek%20to%20hire%20from%20abroad%20again.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHowever%2C%20Lai%20said%20it's%20unclear%20if%20the%20fee%20will%20remain%20struck%20down.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Hung-Lin%20Lai%2C%2034%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Lai%20%26amp%3B%20Turner%20Law%20Firm%20PLLC%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Oklahoma.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20federal%20ruling%20struck%20down%20the%20%24100%2C000%20H-1B%20fee%20on%20Monday%2C%20I%20was%20relieved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20lawyers%20were%20optimistic%20this%20would%20be%20the%20result%2C%20based%20on%20a%20previous%20Supreme%20Court%20ruling%20that%20struck%20down%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-scotus-rules-trump-tariffs-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrump's%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20felt%20the%20administration's%20immigration%20decision%20similarly%20bypassed%20regular%20lawmaking%2C%20so%20it%20was%20unlikely%20to%20remain%20in%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20battle's%20not%20over.%20The%20Trump%20administration%20can%20appeal%20this%20decision%2C%20and%20other%20legal%20challenges%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fh-1b-visa-filings-rise-for-anthropic-openai-nvidia-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20H-1B%20fee%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20still%20moving%20through%20the%20courts.%20The%20judges%20might%20agree%20with%20this%20decision%2C%20or%20rule%20in%20the%20opposite%20direction%2C%20creating%20what's%20called%20a%20%26quot%3Bcircuit%20split.%26quot%3B%20We%20have%20to%20wait%20and%20see%20what%20happens%2C%20as%20a%20decision%20about%20this%20fee%20could%20make%20its%20way%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20H-1B%20visas%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Accheong%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eccheong%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b0c0ebf4-cb77-4e1a-8585-19c31d2bfc8a%5C%22%3EThe%20ruling%20is%20helpful%20for%20small%20businesses%20who%20want%20to%20recruit%20and%20hire%20foreign%20talent%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20H-1B%20fee%20impacted%20small%20and%20medium-sized%20businesses%2C%20like%20mine%2C%20who%20can't%20afford%20to%20pay%20%24100%2C000%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-100k-h-1b-visa-trump-talent-company-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehire%20a%20foreign%20worker%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20for%20big%20companies%20like%20Amazon%20and%20Facebook%2C%20it's%20the%20cost%20of%20doing%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20prospective%20client%20abandoned%20sponsoring%20someone%20for%20an%20H-1B%20visa%20after%20finding%20out%20they'd%20need%20to%20pay%20the%20fee.%20I%20think%20most%20business%20owners%20would%20rather%20invest%20%24100%2C000%20into%20their%20company%20than%20pay%20it%20to%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20employer%2C%20I%20was%20lucky%20to%20hire%20someone%20on%20the%20H-1B%20visa%20before%20the%20%24100%2C000%20fee%20came%20into%20effect.%20But%20we%20want%20to%20sponsor%20more%20people%20who%20are%20abroad.%20Earlier%20this%20year%2C%20I%20entered%20a%20virtual%20staff%20member%20in%20the%20lottery%2C%20but%20told%20her%20that%20if%20she%20were%20picked%20and%20the%20fee%20was%20still%20in%20place%2C%20I%20wouldn't%20be%20in%20a%20position%20to%20pay%20that%20amount.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20she%20hasn't%20been%20selected%2C%20so%20that%20point%20is%20moot%2C%20but%20this%20recent%20ruling%20makes%20me%20more%20willing%20to%20sponsor%20foreign%20team%20members%20in%20the%20future.%20However%2C%20this%20could%20still%20be%20costly%2C%20because%20the%20ruling%20doesn't%20impact%20last%20year's%20changes%20to%20the%20lottery%20system%20favoring%20applicants%20with%20a%20higher%20wage.%20This%20means%20I%20may%20have%20to%20submit%20an%20application%20in%20a%20higher%20wage%20tier%20to%20give%20candidates%20a%20better%20chance%20of%20being%20selected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20still%20discussing%20with%20colleagues%20how%20this%20ruling%20might%20impact%20applicants%20to%20the%20lottery%20for%20the%202027%20fiscal%20year%2C%20and%20whether%20there's%20a%20way%20the%20%24100%2C000%20could%20still%20apply%20to%20them.%20Currently%2C%20the%20%24100%2C000%20fee%20is%20no%20longer%20required%20for%20current%20applications.%20I%20think%20we'll%20see%20the%20ruling%20impact%20the%20following%20year's%20lottery.%20If%20the%20%24100%2C000%20fee%20still%20does%20not%20apply%2C%20we%20might%20see%20an%20uptick%20in%20small%20and%20medium-sized%20businesses%20like%20ours%20being%20willing%20to%20submit%20petitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20helpful%20for%20businesses%20our%20size%2C%20so%20that%20we%20can%20recruit%20and%20hire%20foreign%20talent%2C%20rather%20than%20just%20the%20Amazons%20and%20Facebooks%20being%20able%20to%20hire%20these%20individuals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EA%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20ruling%20was%20%26quot%3Bblatant%20judicial%20activism.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20spokesperson%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20recent%20changes%20to%20the%20H-1B%20visa%20program%2C%20including%20the%20increased%20fee%2C%20are%20intended%20to%20address%20concerns%20about%20program%20integrity%20and%20the%20impact%20on%20the%20U.S.%20workforce.%20The%20policy%20aims%20to%20ensure%20that%20employers%20prioritize%20hiring%20U.S.%20workers%2C%20particularly%20in%20high-skilled%20fields.%20The%20Trump%20Administration%20remains%20committed%20to%20safeguarding%20opportunities%20for%20American%20workers%20and%20maintaining%20the%20integrity%20of%20employment-based%20visa%20programs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flawyer-couldnt-pay-100k-h-1b-visa-opportunities-reopen-scrapped-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1781027354000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a2831ce67142ea6832cde5b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flawyer-couldnt-pay-100k-h-1b-visa-opportunities-reopen-scrapped-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20US-based%20lawyer%20who%20works%20in%20im